{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XnRrmKq21bDXvBCVpvC7hu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### Session 30 — state corruption fix #14, no-op (2026-03-27T19:27Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **State corruption fix #14**: Same pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review`, phantom `1-1-foo` present, counts 75/70.\n     6→- Root cause fix IS in dist/index.js:2313 (`clean.startsWith(\"{\")` guard). The fix was built in session 29's commit.\n     7→- **Why corruption persists**: Ralph likely ran between session 29's commit and this session, using the OLD dist/ before session 29 rebuilt. The corruption is from a previous ralph iteration that ran before the fix was deployed.\n     8→- Fixed: restored all 4 stories to `done`, removed phantom, counts to 74/74.\n     9→- **This should be the LAST occurrence** — the fix is now in dist/ and committed.\n    10→- All 74 stories done. No actionable work. Sprint complete.\n    11→\n    12→## Token Report\n    13→- Total tool calls: ~15\n    14→- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 6, Grep: 3, Glob: 2, Agent: 1, Bash: 1\n    15→- Files read: 4 unique, 6 total reads\n    16→- Redundant operations: Re-read of sprint-status.yaml due to concurrent modification\n    17→\n    18→### Session 29 — state corruption fix #13 + commit root cause fix (2026-03-27T19:22Z)\n    19→\n    20→- **State corruption fix #13**: Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json. Phantom `1-1-foo` re-appeared. sprint.total was 75, sprint.done was 70.\n    21→- **Root cause fix from session 22 was never committed** — the code changes to `ralph.ts` and `state.ts` existed only in the working tree. Ralph runs from committed/built code, so the fix was never active.\n    22→- Fixed: restored all 4 stories to `done`, removed phantom `1-1-foo`, fixed counts to 74/74.\n    23→- This session COMMITS the root cause fix so it persists across ralph iterations.\n    24→- All 152 test suites pass (4018 tests), build clean.\n    25→\n    26→## Token Report\n    27→- Total tool calls: ~18\n    28→- By tool: Read: 6, Edit: 7, Bash: 3, Grep: 1, Write: 1\n    29→- Files read: 4 unique, 7 total reads\n    30→- Redundant operations: One re-read of sprint-status.yaml due to concurrent modification\n    31→\n    32→### Session 22 — ROOT CAUSE FIX APPLIED (2026-03-27T19:30Z)\n    33→\n    34→- **State corruption fix #12**: Restored 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 to `done`, removed phantom `1-1-foo`, fixed sprint counts (75→74 total, 70→74 done).\n    35→- **ROOT CAUSE FIX 1**: Added `if (clean.startsWith('{')) return null;` guard to `parseRalphMessage()` in `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts`. JSON lines (stream-json NDJSON) are now skipped before ralph pattern matching, preventing phantom story creation from test output or source code containing ralph-like patterns.\n    36→- **ROOT CAUSE FIX 2**: Changed `updateStoryStatus()` in `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` to reject unknown story keys instead of creating them via `defaultStoryState()`. Added new `registerStory()` function for explicit story creation during sprint initialization.\n    37→- **Test updates**: Updated `state.test.ts`, `index.test.ts`, and `ralph.test.ts` with `registerStory()` calls and phantom prevention tests.\n    38→- **All 152 test suites pass (4016+ tests), build clean.**\n    39→- This should permanently prevent the state corruption that wasted 12+ sessions and ~$20+ in API calls.\n    40→\n    41→## Token Report\n    42→- Total tool calls: ~30\n    43→- By tool: Read: 10, Edit: 15, Grep: 8, Glob: 3, Agent: 2, Bash: 0\n    44→- Files read: ~8 unique, ~12 total reads (sprint-state.json read 3 times, state.ts read 2 times)\n    45→- Redundant operations: Had to re-read sprint-status.yaml once due to external modification between read and edit\n    46→\n    47→### Session 21 — ROOT CAUSE FOUND for state corruption (2026-03-27T19:15Z)\n    48→\n    49→- **ROOT CAUSE IDENTIFIED**: `parseRalphMessage()` in `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` matches `[SUCCESS] Story {key}: DONE` regex within stream-json NDJSON lines. When claude session output contains tool results or text that includes these patterns (e.g., reading test files, source code, or discussing story completions), the regex matches inside the JSON envelope.\n    50→- `handleAgentEvent()` in `run.ts:41-48` then calls `updateStoryStatus(key, 'review')`, which CREATES new story entries (line 347: `?? defaultStoryState()`) or resets existing `done` stories to `review`.\n    51→- **Evidence**: This session created 3 phantom stories: `16-5-xxx`, `16-5-foo`, `1-1-foo` — all from patterns in session output. The `1-1-foo` came directly from test file `ralph.test.ts` line: `driver.parseOutput('[SUCCESS] Story 1-1-foo: DONE')`.\n    52→- **Fix needed**: `parseRalphMessage()` must NOT match within JSON lines. Add a check: if the line starts with `{`, skip ralph pattern matching entirely (it's a stream-json line, let the stream-json parser handle it).\n    53→- **Secondary fix**: `updateStoryStatus()` should NOT create new story entries. Change `?? defaultStoryState()` to return an error if the story key doesn't exist.\n    54→- Fixed: removed 3 phantom stories, restored sprint counts to 74/74.\n    55→- All 74 real stories remain done.\n    56→\n    57→## Token Report\n    58→- Total tool calls: ~25\n    59→- By tool: Read: 8, Grep: 6, Bash: 5, Edit: 6, Agent: 1\n    60→- Largest Bash outputs: git diff (~80 lines), python3 state fix (~1 line)\n    61→- Files read: ~10 unique, ~15 total reads (sprint-state.json read 4+ times, state.ts read 3 times)\n    62→- Redundant operations: Multiple reads of sprint-state.json as file kept being externally modified\n    63→\n    64→### Session 20 — state corruption fix #11, no-op (2026-03-27T18:50Z)\n    65→\n    66→- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and 10 previous sessions fixing this.\n    67→- Epic-16 at `backlog` in 