{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S8bQqKgpf8ADUjJr557WnK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### Session 31 — state corruption fix #15, no-op (2026-03-27T19:33Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **State corruption fix #15**: Same pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review`, phantom `1-1-foo` present, counts 75/70.\n     6→- `registerStory` guard from session 22 is NOT in dist/ — tree-shaken by tsup. The `startsWith(\"{\")` guard and `updateStoryStatus` phantom rejection ARE in dist/.\n     7→- The phantom `1-1-foo` persists because it was already in sprint-state.json before the fix was deployed. The fix prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't clean up existing ones.\n     8→- Ralph likely reads state at process start, runs an iteration, and writes the stale state back — overwriting our manual fixes.\n     9→- Fixed: removed phantom, restored all 4 stories to `done`, counts to 74/74.\n    10→- All 74 stories done. No actionable work. Sprint complete.\n    11→- **Root cause still active**: ralph's process lifetime spans multiple sessions. It reads state once, and if the state was corrupt when it started, it keeps writing corrupt state. The fix needs to be: either ralph re-reads state from disk before each write, or the phantom is cleaned up at ralph startup.\n    12→\n    13→## Token Report\n    14→- Total tool calls: ~15\n    15→- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 1, Bash: 5, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n    16→- Files read: 5 unique, 7 total reads\n    17→- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of tree-shaking issue\n    18→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SQfQemGi8bbhRNpyFb7XSJ","session_id":"12484742-724e-4cb6-bd97-883b7e6725a8","uuid":"cc8d8012-ec64-4ab3-b003-02193af42d2e","timestamp":"2026-03-27T15:36:33.332Z"}
